The paper proposes a few-shot clustering method and introduces unsupervised few-shot classification, which are both related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions image datasets such as Omniglot and miniImageNet, indicating a focus on computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as clustering text documents, which suggests a possible sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions learning-to-cluster methods, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
